12 §3386.2. Addictive Disorder Regulatory Authority
13 A.(1) The legislature hereby finds it appropriate that the responsibility and
14 authority to regulate the practice of addictive disorder treatment and prevention be
15 exercised by a licensing board created for that purpose.
16 (2) It is the intent of the legislature that there be a single authority
17 issuing credentials for substance use disorder counseling, prevention, and peer
18 support professionals in Louisiana. The authority for issuing and recognizing
19 credentials for professionals engaged in the providing of substance use disorder
20 counseling, prevention, and peer support services for those who suffer from
21 behavioral health conditions shall be the Addictive Disorder Regulatory
22 Authority.
