3 §3387.15. Peer support specialist; scope of practice
4 A.(1) The practice of peer support within the meaning and intent of this
5 Chapter shall consist of the rendering of mentorship, guidance, and support
6 services to individuals suffering from a behavioral health condition to assist
7 them in gaining an understanding of the nature of their disorder and developing
8 and maintaining a responsible lifestyle.
9 (2) The peer support specialist may practice autonomously, independent
10 of any other professional association or supervision. The peer support specialist
11 cannot render clinical services.
12 (3) The scope of practice, in addition to any other applicable provision
13 of this Chapter, shall include implementing strategic support, providing
14 mentorship to family members, and, as appropriate, to others affected by the
15 individual's behavioral health condition, and the utilization of KSA and core
16 functions.
17 B. The board shall adopt and promulgate rules which govern peer
18 support specialists in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter.
